sentences.sentence: Mutual Fund and ETF data provided byRefinitiv Lipper.Independent voters Dominick Ciccarelli and Dennis Richmond Jr. joined 'FOX & Friends' to discuss their take on the upcoming announcement as the 2024 presidential election looms.On Monday, October 9, I declared myself anindependent candidate for presidentof the United States of America.And more than that, I joined my voice with all the people who are fed up and all the people who are hopeful, to make a new Declaration of Independence for our entire nation.On this day,I declared my independencefrom the corporations that have hijacked our government to milk us for profit.RFK JR ANNOUNCES INDEPENDENT RUN FOR PRESIDENT AGAINST BIDENI declared independence from Wall Street, Big Tech, Big Pharma, Big Ag, the military contractors, and their lobbyists who now outnumber members of Congress 20 to 1.I declared independence from the mercenary media that forever urges us to hate our neighbors and fear our friends.I declared independence from the cynical elites who betray our hope and amplify our divisions.And finally, I declared independence from thetwo political partiesand the corrupt interests that dominate them, and the entire rigged system of rancor and rage, corruption and lies, that has turned government officials into indentured servants of their corporate bosses.

If left unchecked, they will commoditize our air, water, food, labor, and children, and turn the American Dream into desperation and dust.I declared my independence from these corrupting powers because they are incompatible with the inalienable rights that our original Declaration of Independence invoked in 1776: life, liberty, and the pursuit of happiness.RFK JR TEASES 'MAJOR ANNOUNCEMENT' AS SPECULATION SWIRLS ABOUT INDEPENDENT RUNHow can we guard life when for-profit corporations have captured the public agencies that are supposed to protect us?
How can we enjoy liberty when a surveillance state seeks to hide the truth and quash dissent to preserve its power?

And how can we pursue happiness when our nation's families are imprisoned by debt and hunger and jobs that will never pay the bills?And so today I declared my independence from the tyranny of corruption which robs us of affordable lives, belief in our future, and respect for one another.
And to do that, I had to declare my independence from the Democratic Party and independence from all parties.I haven't made this decision lightly.

It is painful for me to let go of the party ofmy uncles, my father, of my grandfather and of both of my great-grandfathers ᅳ John "Honey Fitz" Fitzgerald, Boston's first Irish Catholic mayor, and Patrick Kennedy, a Boston ward boss, who together, launched my family's political dynasty.CLICK HERE FOR MORE FOX NEWS OPINIONBut my sacrifice is nothing compared to the risk our founding fathers took when they signed theDeclaration of Independence247 years ago right over there.
They knew that if their revolution failed, every last one of them would be hanged.

They chose to place everything on the line.When John Adams put his pen down after adding his signature to the Declaration, he turned to those present and said, "Sink or swim, live or die, survive or perish, from this day on, I'm with my country."

I make that same pledge today, so that I may stand before you as every leader should ᅳ free of partisan allegiance and backroom wheeling and dealing ᅳ a servant only to my conscience, to my creator, and to you.Former Democratic presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy Jr. on the campaign trail earlier this year.
The son of a former U.S. Attorney General and Democratic candidate declared his candidacy as an independent candidate on October 9, 2023.
(Hans Gutknecht/MediaNews Group/Los Angeles Daily News via Getty Images)On October 9, we are turning a new page in American politics.There have been independent candidates before.
This time, the Independent is going to win.The two major parties are fielding candidates that most Americans do not want even to run.
A shocking three-fourths of Americans believePresident Bidenis too old to govern effectively.
President Trump faces multiple civil and criminal trials.
Both have favorability ratings deep in negative territory.That is what two-party politics has come to, and that is why we need to break the stranglehold of the two parties.

And that's why we need to pry loose the hammerlock of corrupt power over Washington, D.C.We are going to make this nation ours again.Robert F. Kennedy Jr. is an independent candidate for president of the United States.Get the recap of top opinion commentary and original content throughout the week.
